Categorize GUIDES based on the group "Non-target". Use 10th percentile of the ratio in the Non-target group as threshold to label each guide as "Hit" or "Non-hit"

  • First calcualte needed ratios:
    1. Stem later time point vs. Stem before time point: S5/S2
    2. Induced cells vs. stem before time point: S6/S2
    3. Induced cells vs. stem later time point: S6/S5
In [14]:
screen1['r52'] = screen1.S5 / screen1.S2
screen1['r62'] = screen1.S6 / screen1.S2
screen1['r65'] = screen1.S6 / screen1.S5
screen1['r21'] = screen1.S2 / screen1.S1
screen1['r31'] = screen1.S3 / screen1.S1
screen1['r32'] = screen1.S3 / screen1.S2
screen1['r76'] = screen1.S7 / screen1.S6
screen1['r86'] = screen1.S8 / screen1.S6
screen1['r87'] = screen1.S8 / screen1.S7
  • Criteria and steps to be selected as hits:
    1. calculate 10th percentile of previously calculated fold change of the non-target group as depletion criteria
    2. label guide RNAs as hit if fold change is less than set threshold

# label guide RNAs
screen1['r52flag'] = screen1['r52'].apply(lambda x: 'Hit' if x < rna_cutoffs['r52'] else 'Non-hit') # deplete
screen1['r62flag'] = screen1['r62'].apply(lambda x: 'Hit' if x < rna_cutoffs['r62'] else 'Non-hit') # deplete
screen1['r65flag'] = screen1['r65'].apply(lambda x: 'Hit' if x < rna_cutoffs['r65'] else 'Non-hit') # deplete
screen1['r21flag'] = screen1['r21'].apply(lambda x: 'Hit' if x < rna_cutoffs['r21'] else 'Non-hit') # deplete
screen1['r31flag'] = screen1['r31'].apply(lambda x: 'Hit' if x < rna_cutoffs['r31'] else 'Non-hit') # deplete
screen1['r32flag'] = screen1['r32'].apply(lambda x: 'Hit' if x < rna_cutoffs['r32'] else 'Non-hit') # deplete
screen1['r76flag'] = screen1['r76'].apply(lambda x: 'Hit' if x < rna_cutoffs['r76'] else 'Non-hit') # deplete
screen1['r86flag'] = screen1['r86'].apply(lambda x: 'Hit' if x > rna_cutoffs['r86'] else 'Non-hit') # enrich
screen1['r87flag'] = screen1['r87'].apply(lambda x: 'Hit' if x > rna_cutoffs['r87'] else 'Non-hit') # enrich
